\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 In a small {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/saucepan/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 saucepan}} combine the sugar with 1/2 cup water. Bring to a boil over medium heat, then remove from the heat and let cool.\
In a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/blender/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 blender}} add the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/watermelon/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 watermelon}}, 2 tablespoons of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/sugar-syrup/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 sugar syrup}} and the lemon juice and puree until smooth. Strain through fine mesh sieve into a bowl and discard the pulp.\
Fill a pitcher with ice, add the watermelon mixture and stir until chilled. Pour into chilled {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/martini/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 martini}} glasses and top with seltzer. Add vodka, if desired.\
